üìå SKILL SPECIFICATION: CV SCREENING
1. Purpose of the Skill

The ability to evaluate and filter CVs in a:

Structured and systematic way

Objective (non-emotional, non-biased)

Criteria-driven

Time-efficient while maintaining shortlist quality

I. Core Competencies
1. JD Structuring Ability
Description

Ability to break down a Job Description into 4 clear categories:

Must-have ‚Äì Non-negotiable requirements

Core competencies ‚Äì 70% of hiring decision weight

Nice-to-have ‚Äì Value-added qualifications

Red flags ‚Äì Potential risk indicators

Proficiency Indicators

Creates a fixed evaluation checklist before reviewing CVs

Applies consistent criteria across candidates

Avoids brand-name bias

Maturity Levels

Junior: Reads JD descriptively

Mid-level: Categorizes requirements clearly

Senior: Refines JD structure to improve screening accuracy and risk prediction

2. Rapid Screening (30‚Äì60 seconds per CV)
Description

Ability to eliminate 50‚Äì70% of unsuitable CVs quickly by checking:

Minimum years of experience

Relevant industry/role alignment

Directly related job functions

Abnormal job-hopping patterns (e.g., 3‚Äì6 month tenures)

Performance Indicators

Maximum 1 minute per CV (initial screening)

At least 60% of shortlisted candidates pass the main interview

Common Mistakes

Over-reading too early

Being influenced by visual design

Letting prestige override relevance

3. Structured Scoring & Quantitative Evaluation
Description

Ability to design and apply a weighted scoring framework.

Example Framework
Criteria	Weight
Relevant Experience	30%
Technical/Functional Skills	30%
Measurable Achievements	20%
Growth Mindset / Learning	10%
Employment Stability	10%
Scoring Scale

1 = Very weak

3 = Meets expectations

5 = Exceptional

Standards

Eliminate candidates scoring below 60%

Justify evaluation decisions with clear reasoning

4. Deep Review & Pattern Recognition

(For top 20‚Äì30% candidates)

Focus Areas

Results vs Responsibilities

Weak: ‚ÄúManaged marketing team‚Äù

Strong: ‚ÄúIncreased traffic by 120% in 6 months‚Äù

Ownership Level

Led independently

Co-owned

Supported

Career Logic

Logical progression

Industry switching rationale

Unexplained downgrades

Advanced Capability (Senior Level)

Predict performance risk

Identify early attrition risk

Assess adaptability to startup or high-growth environments

5. Culture & Motivation Assessment
Indicators to Look For

Side projects

Leadership roles

Public speaking or writing

Cross-functional exposure

For Startup or Agile Environments

Prioritize candidates with:

Experience in smaller organizations

Multi-tasking capability

Self-built achievements

Strong ownership mindset

6. Pre-Screen Interview Skill (10‚Äì15 Minutes)
Objectives

Verify CV information

Assess communication clarity

Validate motivation

Align salary expectations

Standard Questions

Why did you leave your most recent role?

What project are you most proud of?

What are your salary expectations?

Are you currently interviewing elsewhere?

KPI

Reduce failure rate in formal interviews

Detect misalignment before advancing candidates

II. Behavioral Indicators
Strong CV Screener

Speaks in data (‚ÄúCandidate scored 78%‚Äù)

Documents elimination reasons clearly

Uses consistent scoring criteria

Reviews CVs in batches to reduce bias

Compares candidates against JD, not against each other

Weak CV Screener

Relies on gut feeling

Overvalues company brand names

Changes evaluation criteria per candidate

Gets influenced by design or formatting

III. Performance KPIs
Metric	Strong Benchmark
Screening Time	‚â§ 1 min per CV (initial round)
Interview Pass Rate	‚â• 60%
Offer Acceptance Rate	‚â• 70%
Early Attrition (First 3 months)	‚â§ 15%
IV. Competency Maturity Levels
Level 1 ‚Äì Basic Screener

Screens based mainly on years of experience

Prone to bias

No structured scoring system

Level 2 ‚Äì Structured Screener

Uses weighted scoring

Screens in batches

Can justify decisions clearly

Level 3 ‚Äì Strategic Talent Filter

Predicts long-term performance

Identifies high-potential talent

Refines JD to improve talent pipeline quality

Optimizes CV ‚Üí Interview ‚Üí Offer conversion

V. Core Evaluation Formula

Candidate Fit = (Capability √ó Results √ó Stability) + Motivation

If one of the first three factors is weak ‚Üí High performance risk
If motivation is weak ‚Üí High attrition risk
